
WOW64 = *→ Windows on Windows 64 bit*.

Purpose: allow 32 bit applications to run on a 64 bit Windows environment.

→ Windows/development/Portable-Executable/DLL[DLLs]:
  • `Wow64.dll`
  • `Wow64win.dll` (Entry points for 32 bit applications)
  • `Wow64cpu.dll` (switch → hardware/CPUs/x86[CPU] between 32 and 64 bit)
  • `Ntdll.dell`
  •  etc.

{ Environment variables

  The values of some → development/endianness[environment variables] are dependent on the bitness of process that uses them.

table { lll

    → development/environment-variable[environment variable] ☰ 32 bit → Windows/development/process[process]           ☰ 64 bit process
    `PROCESSOR_ARCHITECTURE`                                 ☰ `x86`                                                   ☰ `AMD64` or `IA64` or `ARM64`
    `PROCESSOR_ARCHITEW6432`                                 ☰ `%PROCESSOR_ARCHITECTURE%`                              ☰ n/a
    `ProgramFiles`                                           ☰ → Windows/dirs/Program-Files-x86[`%ProgramFies(x86)%`]  ☰ `%ProgramFiles%`
    `ProgramW6432`                                           ☰ `%ProgramFiles%`                                        ☰ `%CommonProgramFiles%`
    `CommonProgramFiles`                                     ☰ `%CommonProgramFiles(x86)%`                             ☰ `%CommonProgramFiles%`
    `CommonProgramW6432`                                     ☰ `%CommonProgramFiles%`                                  ☰ `%CommonProgramFiles%`

table }

}

sa:
  → Windows/registry[Registry] key → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/Software/Wow6432Node[`HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Wow6432Node`]

  → Windows/cmd-exe/tasks/determine-if-32-or-64-bit-Windows
